The paper discusses the use of neural networks for data structure optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed Neural Bloom Filter also involves memory architecture, which is a topic in computer science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the Neural Bloom Filter in computer vision (cs.CV).
